  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Seed Vouchers, Cash Grants And Silc in Yatenga Province (VOCSY)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The 2011-2012 agricultural season in the northern region of Burkina Faso was particularly catastrophic, resulting in a very precarious food security situation for inhabitants of the region.  In response, CRS initiated the VOCSY project (Seed Vouchers, Cash Grants and Savings and Internal Lending Communities (SILC) in Yatenga Province), and works with its partner OCADES Ouahigouya to distribute cash grants to 3,300 beneficiaries, provide seed vouchers to 8,800 beneficiaries, and establish SILC groups with 8,000 members.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">VOCSY will support the government&#x2019;s goals in agriculture, namely the dissemination and use of improved seed varieties to increase crop production and the development of commodity value chains, with  three major project components:
-	CASH GRANTS will allow households to meet some of their immediate needs and support local market systems.
-	THE DISTRIBUTION OF SEED VOUCHERS will give farmers access to improved seed for the coming season, better prospects at harvest, and replenished seed stocks for the future.  
These two components will be made sustainable through the third component,
-	SILC, which gives beneficiaries a savings structure as well as the chance to develop revenue generating activities and reinforces their financial management and organizational skills.</narrative>
  </description>
